# Testing Strategy ‚Äî Unit ¬∑ Integration ¬∑ E2E

## The Testing Trophy

Prioritise tests by **value-to-cost ratio**:

```
        /‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ\
       /   E2E (few)   \       ‚Üê High confidence, slow, brittle
      /‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ\
     / Integration (some) \    ‚Üê Best ROI ‚Äî test real behaviour
    /‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ\
   /    Unit (many)         \  ‚Üê Fast, isolated, cheap
  /‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ‚Äæ\
 /   Static Analysis (always) \‚Üê TypeScript, linting, type checking
```

- **Most** of your tests should be integration tests ‚Äî they give the highest confidence per test written
- Unit tests for pure functions, algorithms, and complex business logic
- E2E tests for critical user journeys only ‚Äî not for every feature

---

## Core Principles

- Test **behaviour, not implementation** ‚Äî tests should not break when you refactor internals
- One test asserts **one thing** ‚Äî a failing test should point directly to the problem
- Tests must be **deterministic** ‚Äî the same test always produces the same result (no random data, no time dependencies without mocking)
- Tests must be **independent** ‚Äî no shared mutable state between tests; each test arranges its own data
- Tests should be **fast** ‚Äî unit tests in ms, integration tests in seconds; slow tests get skipped
- **Never test the framework** ‚Äî don't write tests to verify that `express` or `django` works; test your logic

---

## Unit Tests

### What to Unit Test
- Pure functions with complex logic (calculations, transformations, validators)
- Domain/service classes in isolation
- Edge cases, boundary values, error conditions that are hard to trigger at a higher level

### What NOT to Unit Test
- Simple getters/setters with no logic
- Framework glue code (route wiring, DI module setup)
- Code whose only behaviour is calling another function

### Rules
- Mock **only at boundaries**: external I/O (HTTP, DB, file system, time, random) ‚Äî not internal collaborators
- Use **`vi.fn()` / `jest.fn()` / `unittest.mock`** for mocks; avoid heavy mocking frameworks
- Follow **AAA** (Arrange, Act, Assert) structure in every test:
  ```ts
  it('calculates total with discount applied', () => {
    // Arrange
    const cart = createCart([{ price: 100, qty: 2 }]);
    // Act
    const total = calculateTotal(cart, { discount: 0.1 });
    // Assert
    expect(total).toBe(180);
  });
  ```
- Name tests with the pattern: `<unit> <condition> <expected outcome>`
  - ‚úÖ `"calculateTotal with 10% discount returns 180"`
  - ‚ùå `"test1"` or `"works correctly"`

