## Integration Tests

### What to Integration Test
- Controller ‚Üí Service ‚Üí Repository ‚Üí real DB (use an in-memory or test DB)
- Full HTTP request/response cycle for API endpoints
- Queue consumers and event handlers
- Auth middleware + protected route

### Rules
- Use **real implementations** for all layers; mock only external third-party services (Stripe, SendGrid, etc.)
- Use a **dedicated test database** ‚Äî never run tests against production or dev data
- **Reset state** between tests (transaction rollback, truncation, or test containers)
- Use **TestContainers** or **Docker Compose** service containers in CI for real DB/Redis instances
- Test **HTTP contracts**: correct status codes, response shape, headers, error bodies

#### Node.js / NestJS
```ts
// Use Supertest for Express / NestJS HTTP integration
const res = await request(app).post('/users').send({ email: 'a@b.com' });
expect(res.status).toBe(201);
expect(res.body).toMatchObject({ id: expect.any(Number), email: 'a@b.com' });
```

#### Python / FastAPI
```python
# Use httpx.AsyncClient with ASGITransport
async with AsyncClient(transport=ASGITransport(app=app), base_url="http://test") as client:
    response = await client.post("/users", json={"email": "a@b.com"})
assert response.status_code == 201
```

