## End-to-End (E2E) Tests

### What to E2E Test
- The 3‚Äì5 most critical user journeys: sign up, log in, complete a purchase, submit a form
- Cross-service flows that cannot be tested in isolation
- Accessibility and visual regressions (optional)

### What NOT to E2E Test
- Every feature ‚Äî E2E tests are expensive to write and maintain
- Negative/edge cases ‚Äî cover these at unit/integration level

### Tools
- **Playwright** (preferred) or Cypress for browser-based E2E
- **k6** or **Locust** for load / performance testing

### Rules
- Run E2E tests against a **deployed staging environment**, not localhost
- Keep E2E test count **small** (< 20 core journeys) ‚Äî quality over quantity
- Use **page object models** to abstract UI selectors from test logic
- Make tests **retry-safe** ‚Äî avoid fixed `sleep()`; use `waitFor` / `expect(locator).toBeVisible()`
- Store E2E test results and screenshots as CI artefacts on failure

